# Next.js 16 + TypeScript

- This repo runs Next.js 16.2.5 — it has breaking changes versus the Next 15
  in most training data and tutorials. Before writing framework code, check
  `docs/Next16_Delta_Notes.md` and the bundled docs at
  `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
- Middleware is now Proxy: the file is `proxy.ts` exporting `proxy`. When any
  guide says "add middleware", write `proxy.ts`.
- Caching: prefer the Cache Components model (`'use cache'` + `cacheLife` +
  `cacheTag`) for reference-data fetchers; classic ISR
  (`export const revalidate`) works only while `cacheComponents` is off.
- App Router only. Server Components by default; add "use client" only when
  interactivity is required.
- Strict TS: no any, no non-null assertions to silence errors. Explicit return
  types on exported functions.
- Validate all external input with zod at the boundary (server AND client).
- Consistent API shape: return { data, error, meta } with explicit error types.
- Core domain logic (scoring, strand validation) lives in pure modules under
  `src/lib/riasec/` — deterministic, side-effect-free, exhaustively unit
  tested. UI never re-implements or hard-codes their rules.
- Comments: one sentence, no emojis, only for non-obvious intent.
